<div class="page-header"><h1>About the campaign</h1>
<p>ACC4PF is a community-led effort to bring Austin Community College in-district for all Pflugerville ISD residents.</p></div>
<div class="prose">

<h2>What we are doing</h2>
<p>We are collecting petition signatures from PfISD-area registered voters to place an ACC annexation measure on the November 2026 ballot. If the petition qualifies and the measure passes, all PfISD residents become part of the ACC taxing district, receiving in-district tuition rates and full ACC district benefits in exchange for paying the ACC property tax.</p>

<h2>Who we are</h2>
<p>ACC4PF is organized by Pflugerville ISD residents who believe our community should have the same access to affordable community college as Round Rock, Leander, Manor, Hays, Elgin, Del Valle, and Lockhart. [Add organizer names and bios as appropriate.]</p>

<h2>What we are not</h2>
<p>This campaign is <strong>independent of Austin Community College</strong>. ACC cannot advocate for or against annexation. ACC may respond to factual questions, but the decision rests entirely with voters. ACC4PF uses publicly available ACC data with attribution and links to original sources.</p>
<p>This is not a partisan campaign. We do not endorse candidates or parties. We support a single ballot measure: bringing ACC in-district for Pflugerville.</p>

<h2>Transparency</h2>
<p>Every data point on this site links to its source. Our <a href="/research/">Research and Sources</a> page provides the full citation list. If we get something wrong, we will correct it publicly and promptly. If you find an error, <a href="/volunteer/">contact us</a>.</p>
<p>Campaign finance reports are filed as required by Texas law and will be posted here when available.</p>

<div class="callout"><strong>Required disclaimer:</strong> Paid for by ACC4PF. Independent of Austin Community College.</div>
